{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17594498","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17594498"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T10:48:51+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T10:48:51+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15317"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15317","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15317"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.09,0.06,0.12,0.73,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8008"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80820"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8008","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8008"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15317"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"66141"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"8755"},{"type":"tags","id":"8762"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19465"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27614"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80820","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/80820"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EPrimary sclerosing cholangitis is a chronic liver disease and is characterised by inflammation and scarring of the bile ducts.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is most characteristic of primary sclerosing cholangitis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Affects only intrahepatic bile ducts","Usually presents with acute liver failure","Shows normal alkaline phosphatase levels","Progressive fibrosis of bile ducts","Occurs only in older patients"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EPrimary sclerosing cholangitis (PSC) is characterised by \u003Cstrong\u003Eprogressive fibrosis of bile ducts\u003C/strong\u003E, affecting both intrahepatic and extrahepatic ducts. The suggestion that it \u003Cstrong\u003Eaffects only intrahepatic bile ducts\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EPSC typically has a chronic progressive course rather than \u003Cstrong\u003Epresenting with acute liver failure\u003C/strong\u003E. Laboratory findings usually show elevated alkaline phosphatase and gamma-glutamyl transferase, not \u003Cstrong\u003Enormal alkaline phosphatase levels\u003C/strong\u003E. The disease can affect people of any age, not just \u003Cstrong\u003Eolder\u003C/strong\u003E individuals.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe condition may be asymptomatic in early stages and is often discovered incidentally through abnormal liver function tests. It is commonly associated with inflammatory bowel disease, particularly ulcerative colitis.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Primary sclerosing cholangitis causes progressive fibrosis of both intrahepatic and extrahepatic bile ducts","Laboratory findings in primary sclerosing cholangitis typically show elevated alkaline phosphatase and gamma-glutamyl transferase","Primary sclerosing cholangitis can be asymptomatic in early stages and is often discovered incidentally"],"references":["Joseph A, Samant H. Jaundice. 2023 Aug 8. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 31334972","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science","Gasmi B, Kleiner DE. Liver Histology: Diagnostic and Prognostic Features. Clin Liver Dis. 2020 Feb;24(1):61-74. doi: 10.1016/j.cld.2019.09.004. Epub 2019 Oct 31. PMID: 31753251; PMCID: PMC6986808","Rabiee A, Silveira MG. Primary sclerosing cholangitis. Transl Gastroenterol Hepatol. 2021 Apr 5;6:29. doi: 10.21037/tgh-20-266. PMID: 33824933; PMCID: PMC7829069."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"66141"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15317"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"66141","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/66141"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-23T09:26:08+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-23T09:27:28+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8008"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80820"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4928","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/t